FBIS4-60819 "drsov084_a_94010" FBIS-SOV-94-084 Daily Report 30 Apr 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Condemns Stalinist Repressions Condemns Stalinist Repressions LD3004123194 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1113 GMT 30 Apr 94 LD3004123194 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service Russian BFN [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondents Anna Melnikova, Yuriy Sizov] [Text] Moscow, 30 Apr -- Russia once again declares that it condemns the Stalinist repressions against independent Latvia, Boris Yeltsin said in the Kremlin today after the signing of a package of Russian-Latvian documents. Latvian President Guntis Ulmanis thanked Boris Yeltsin for this gesture. For the inhabitants of Latvia these are very generous and fine words, which will help us to come to terms with many psychological contradictions that have been created during these decades, he said.
